  "instruction": "A network has 5 computers with the following number of connections (degree) each: {deg_list}. How many total connection cables are used (i.e., how many edges)?",
  "params": {
    "degrees": {
      "type": "choice",
      "choices": [
        [2,3,3,4,2],
        [4,4,3,3,2],
        [1,2,3,4,2],
        [3,2,2,2,3],
        [4,3,2,3,2],
        [2,2,3,3,4],
        [1,3,4,4,2],
        [2,4,4,2,2]
      ]
    }
  },
  "answer_expr": "graphdeg160",
  "steps": [
    "Each cable (edge) contributes 1 to each endpoint's degree, so it counts twice.",
    "Total degree sum = {deg_sum}.",
    "Number of cables = {deg_sum} / 2 = {answer_graphdeg160}."
  ],
  "tags": ["graph-theory", "handshaking-theorem", "network", "applied"]
}
